Then take pure wax which, placed near the lire, you will strongly pound, aud, thus warm, you will place it upon the table between the two woods, water being first applied that they may not adhere; and pass- ing over it the wetted round wood strongly with both hands, you will thin it according to the thickness of the picces of wood. And when you have prepared many even pieccs of wax, sitting near the lire, cut them small according to the spaces which you had cut in the clay of the censer, aud you will adjust to each space its piace slightly warmed, and with an iron, fit for this work, and made warm, you will solder it round.
